The Perfect Blow Out - using the @dyson_india Airwrap!

Products used:
- @kerastase_official Ultime Elixir
- Wide Tooth Comb
- @dyson_india @dysonhair Airwrap

Product Suggestions:
- @bbluntindia Hot Shot Heat Protection Mist (before blow dry)
- @schwarzkopfin OSIS+ hair mousse (on wet hair)
- @lorealparis @lorealpro Elnett Spray (after curling)

Tips:
- always work with slightly damp hair
- use small sections (yes it takes longer but the styling will last longer)
- use a heat protectant spray if desired
- expect the curls to open up a bit because it is not a curling tong. It is meant to look like a blow out (and not tight curls)
- use a serum and hairspray to control frizz 
- use the flat brush before the curling barrels to reduce frizz if needed 

Let me know if this helps! Ask me any questions in the comments :)

Ok let’s be real.. this is my routine every time I leave the house, even if I’m not in college or office! 🤷‍♀️

Products used:
•⁠ @dotandkey.skincare Strawberry Dew Tinted Sunscreen (Sand) - Yay for a tinted sunscreen that actually makes you want to use it!! #ad
•⁠ @nudestix Cream Blush (Dirty 30) 
•⁠ @calvinklein Sheer Beauty EDP

Am I missing anything? What is your quick routine like?👇🏼

Here’s the low down..

- Tinted moisturisers, serum foundations or anything lightweight and hydrating is a great first step for coverage. I’ve used the @lorealparis serum foundation and it is FABULOUS. 

- Your first concealer should either match your skin perfectly or be a tiny bit warmer/darker. Or if you need a colour corrector then you can use that! Only. Where. It’s. Needed. Please. Again this super thin concealer from @lorealparis has quickly become my favourite!

- Liquid blushes have my heart this year. And a berry toned one? Yes please! You only need a tiny tiny amount so don’t go ham or you’ll like a berry yourself. This blush is from… yep you guessed it - @lorealparis 

- Okay this lighter concealer needs to be dealt with carefully. Don’t go crazy or you’ll look patchy and strange. A tiny amount under your eyes and centre of the face is all you need to give you dimension. Concealer from.. yep you know the drill. 

- Powders are non negotiable. I’ll say it again for those in denial. NON NEGOTIABLE. Powders are not the reason your makeup looks cakey. I promise you. So stop avoiding them. Infact it can make your makeup look 10x better. And powder puffs are the way to go especially for your under eyes. Powder from @milanicosmeticsuk because it’s so so so good!!

- Cream highlighters are the key to making your skin look fresh and healthy and dewy. I’m over powder highlighters (not really but you know what I mean). The cream formula makes it look like skin again and adding just a tiny bit in specific parts of your face that catch the light can be a game changer. Stick highlighter from *drumrolls* @lorealparis 

Was this helpful? Tell me what you’re struggling with so I can help you!!👇🏼

Bouncy blow outs will always be in🤷‍♀️

Played around with @dyson newer Airwrap attachments and their pre styling cream for the first time here! Whilst I still need to test out their styling creams a bit more to see if I love it, the newer attachments have my heart. 🫶

Love that I can just switch sides on the same barrel and the flyaway attachment got rid of the frizz and fly away immediately!!😍

The big round blow out brush looks promising because the bounce it gave my bangs in less than a minute was 10/10. I’m going to use it on my whole head next - to see how that works haha! 😁

The big question everyone has.. did this style hold? It looked good for the whole day. The next morning and for 2-3 days after, the curls/waves were pretty much gone but my hair still looked blow dried and had a nice shape! 😌

I need to test out the Chitosan pre styling cream a few more times to decide if it works for me or not. Stay tuned for more reviews and videos😍
